The paper discusses the use of random dynamical networks as alternative computing architectures for future information processing devices. This topic falls under the category of "Emerging Technologies" (cs.ET) as it deals with the development of new computing architectures for nanoelectronics. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these networks for information processing, which falls under the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the robustness and scalability of these networks, which falls under the category of "Systems and Control" (cs.SY). The manufacturing benefits of these networks for bottom-up designed devices suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of "Digital Circuits" (cs.DC) and "Architecture" (cs.AR).
